  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>"Today"</td>
    <td>29</td>
    <td>36</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>"Vote"</td>
    <td>23</td>
    <td>15</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>"America"</td>
    <td>17</td>
    <td>70</td>
  </tr>
</table>

<p>In today's political climate, it's easy to take sides and never look at another person's point of view that differs from your own. With this project, I want to break that cycle and focus on what brings us together, rather than tears us apart. Donald Trump's public discourse may carry a different tone and support different policies than Barack Obama's, but he still has some similar values to our former president. Both men spend time on Twitter talking about the "people" of our country and "America" as a whole. They both urged us to "vote" and realize that our voices count in this democracy. They both have aimed to stay current, highlighting what's going on "today" and both men have used Twitter as a platform to personally "thank" us. Although this data is only a small insight into an enormous topic, it highlights the fact that even in the face of seemingly insurrmountable differences, you may find some unexpected similarities.</p>
